MALAPP Age Depth Modeling and Pollen Diagrams

This is an R Markdown Notebook. When you execute code within the notebook, the results appear beneath the code.

This document provides code used to build age depth models and pollen diagrams for sediment samples from the Malawi Ancient Lifeways and Peoples Project (MALAPP).

Load packages

library(rbacon)
## Loading required package: IntCal
library(rioja)
## This is rioja 0.9-26

AU8 age depth model

Bacon(core="AU8",d.min=0,d.max=146,accept.suggestions = TRUE,verbose=FALSE)

# Note: Bacon requires user input to command line (typically "y" then enter).

AU8 pollen depths and diagram

core<-rep("AU8",7)
pollenNo<-c("POL35","POL34","POL33","POL32","POL31","POL30","POL29")
depth<-c(11,45,59,74,86,110,146)
ageBP<-c()
ageMin<-c()
ageMax<-c()
for (i in depth){
  ageBP<-append(ageBP,round(mean(Bacon.Age.d(i))))
  ageMin<-append(ageMin,round(min(Bacon.Age.d(i))))
  ageMax<-append(ageMax,round(max(Bacon.Age.d(i))))
}
AUG8data<-data.frame(core,pollenNo,depth,ageBP,ageMin,ageMax)
print(AUG8data)
##   core pollenNo depth ageBP ageMin ageMax
## 1  AU8    POL35    11  1654   1200   2290
## 2  AU8    POL34    45  6500   3816   9054
## 3  AU8    POL33    59  8578   7697   9798
## 4  AU8    POL32    74 10870   9325  11784
## 5  AU8    POL31    86 18931  17476  19571
## 6  AU8    POL30   110 23995  19866  33012
## 7  AU8    POL29   146 31277  22663  44397

AU8 pollen diagram

AUG8pollen<-read.csv("Aug8Pollen.csv",stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
pollenData<-AUG8pollen[,6:ncol(AUG8pollen)]
cs<-colSums(pollenData)
pollenData2 <- pollenData[, which(cs > 5)]

#png("AU8pollen.png",width=6,height=3,units="in",res=600)
par(oma=c(4,4,3,4))
strat.plot(pollenData2,yvar=round(ageBP), y.tks=c(0,5000,10000,15000,20000,25000,30000,35000), y.rev=TRUE, plot.line=FALSE, plot.poly=TRUE, plot.bar=FALSE, col.poly="forestgreen", col.poly.line="white", lwd.poly=1, scale.percent=TRUE, xSpace=0.01, x.pc.lab=TRUE, x.pc.omit0=TRUE,cex.xlabel=0.4,cex.axis=0.5,cex.yaxis=0.5,ylabel = "Years BP",cex.ylabel=0.5,srt.xlabel=45,title="AU8",las=3,mgp=c(3,0.6,0))

#dev.off()

# Note: Bacon requires user input to command line (typically "y" then enter).

AU7 pollen depths

core<-rep("AU7",9)
pollenNo<-c("POL36","POL37","POL38","POL39","POL40","POL41","POL42","POL43","POL44")
depth<-c(6,15,26,32,42,51,54,66,77)
ageBP<-c()
ageMin<-c()
ageMax<-c()
for (i in depth){
  ageBP<-append(ageBP,round(mean(Bacon.Age.d(i))))
  ageMin<-append(ageMin,round(min(Bacon.Age.d(i))))
  ageMax<-append(ageMax,round(max(Bacon.Age.d(i))))
}
AUG7data<-data.frame(core,pollenNo,depth,ageBP,ageMin,ageMax)
print(AUG7data)
##   core pollenNo depth ageBP ageMin ageMax

AU7 pollen diagram

AUG7pollen<-read.csv("Aug7Pollen.csv",stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
pollenData<-AUG7pollen[,6:ncol(AUG7pollen)]
cs<-colSums(pollenData)
pollenData2 <- pollenData[, which(cs > 5)]

#png("AU7pollen.png",width=6,height=3,units="in",res=600)
par(oma=c(4,4,3,4))
strat.plot(pollenData2,yvar=round(ageBP), y.tks=c(0,500,1000,1500,2000,2500), y.rev=TRUE, plot.line=FALSE, plot.poly=TRUE, plot.bar=FALSE, col.poly="forestgreen", col.poly.line="white", lwd.poly=1, scale.percent=TRUE, xSpace=0.01, x.pc.lab=TRUE, x.pc.omit0=TRUE,cex.xlabel=0.4,cex.axis=0.5,cex.yaxis=0.5,ylabel = "Years BP",cex.ylabel=0.5,srt.xlabel=45,title="AU7",las=3,mgp=c(3,0.6,0))

# Note: Bacon requires user input to command line (typically "y" then enter).

AU3 pollen depths

core<-rep("AU3",9)
pollenNo<-c("POL11","POL10","POL9","POL8","POL12","POL13","POL16","POL14","POL15")
depth<-c(3,14,19,28,34,40,46,55,67)
ageBP<-c()
ageMin<-c()
ageMax<-c()
for (i in depth){
  ageBP<-append(ageBP,round(mean(Bacon.Age.d(i))))
  ageMin<-append(ageMin,round(min(Bacon.Age.d(i))))
  ageMax<-append(ageMax,round(max(Bacon.Age.d(i))))
}
AUG3data<-data.frame(core,pollenNo,depth,ageBP,ageMin,ageMax)
print(AUG3data)
##   core pollenNo depth ageBP ageMin ageMax

AU3 pollen diagram

AUG3pollen<-read.csv("Aug3Pollen.csv",stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
pollenData<-AUG3pollen[,6:ncol(AUG3pollen)]
pollenData[is.na(pollenData)] <- 0
cs<-colSums(pollenData)
pollenData2 <- pollenData[, which(cs > 5)]

#png("AU7pollen.png",width=6,height=3,units="in",res=600)
par(oma=c(4,4,3,4))
strat.plot(pollenData2,yvar=round(ageBP), y.tks=c(0,500,1000,1500,2000,2500), y.rev=TRUE, plot.line=FALSE, plot.poly=TRUE, plot.bar=FALSE, col.poly="forestgreen", col.poly.line="white", lwd.poly=1, scale.percent=TRUE, xSpace=0.01, x.pc.lab=TRUE, x.pc.omit0=TRUE,cex.xlabel=0.4,cex.axis=0.5,cex.yaxis=0.5,ylabel = "Years BP",cex.ylabel=0.5,srt.xlabel=45,title="AU3",las=3,mgp=c(3,0.6,0))

#dev.off()
